metadata.name: FluxMongers #5
metadata.description:
FluxMongers are very old beings from another dimension and their spin produces huge amounts of energy and this energy discharge is what causes the realities of MAGNETIK to be distorted or even to be torn apart. Their ethereal nature, speed and might make their movements almost to be perceived as some kind of choreography but this can only be called a dance of destruction. What you are looking at is a frame frozen in their deadly dance…

FluxMongers were inspired by light paintings where the painter uses one or few sources of light to draw in the air very quickly and the drawing is captured by long exposure.

After going live,

- press ‘1’ to get a hi-res version and ‘2’ to get a medium-res version (hopefully it will work :/)

- press 's' to save a png

metadata.name: TENDER Pass #846
metadata.description:
Tender is a curatorial platform and community that helps bring incredible works of generative art to discerning collectors.

Holding a TENDER Pass enables enriched benefits and experiences within the Tender ecosystem. Passholders expand their access to unique collaborations with extraordinary artists, indispensable collector tools, curatorial experiences, artwork insights, fine art prints, a thriving community, and more.

Tender is committed to stewarding the growth of generative art and amplifying the voices of artists and collectors across the entire lifecycle: from creation to collection to curation, and back again. Every Pass minted and resold directly enables Tender to continue creating the platform and experiences that serve this mission.

——

TENDER Pass features unique artwork by punevyr. While all Passes are special, a small number of randomly generated, rarified tokens will come with boosted benefits. If you have a piece with a dark background of any kind, you likely possess one of the following:

Bonus Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Bonus trait get 1 guaranteed reserve spot on all TENDER x Collab projects

Grail Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Grail trait get 2 free mints on all TENDER x Collab projects


New Passholders may access our Discord server that’s linked from our website.
For TENDER Pass benefits and up-to-date details, please visit tender.art/pass


Artwork created with p5.js

---

TENDER x punevyr
July 2022

metadata.name: Celebration in Times of Measure #186
metadata.description:
Intentionally developed by placing constraints on the process.

Everything is generated by code written in P5js.

Press '1' for the default, textured version
Press '2' to add outlines and see the form structure

Press '3' to see a flat, untextured version
Press '4' to add outlines (flat version)

Press 'e' to end/skip the initial animation
Press 'r' to restart/replay the animation
Press 's' to save current image (in live view)

Created by Walter Anderson (@noxiarb)

metadata.name: Divisio(X) #350
metadata.description:
On a dynamic grid (2x2, 3x3, 4x4, 5x5 or 6x6), each cell is filled with one shape (out of 6). For each shape, a rotation (0°, 90°, 180°, 270°) and a stroke weight (from 5 to 100) are applied. A color palette (out of 6) and a number of layers (1 to 3) are applied to the canvas.

The background under the shape can be filled by cells, rows or columns. At times, a thick grid may also be visible.	

Generative abstract compositions. Coded in January 2022.

metadata.name: 𝐃𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐡 #70
metadata.description:
Witness hundreds of small geometric objects gather under one roof to create a cosmic rain!

Ever since I was a child, I have always been good with geometric objects. I used to draw objects such as cubes, cylinders and prisms on paper for hours. As if I'm getting lost in every line between those geometric objects! In this way, every detail of geometry in my daily life and in my other existing life attracts my attention.

Recently, I have been doing research on colors and color palettes, it is really impressive how thousands of color mixtures affect each other and the psychology of living things!

∽∽depending on the screen size you can get different resolutions, which brings out a different side of the project! so you can run this project on all screen sizes and get the output!∽∽

Key:
- Press "s" to export an PNG image


Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Memory Module #251
metadata.description:
Day by day, memories accumulate and shape our dreams, subconscious, ideals, and ultimately, the innermost self. 

This artwork is created by repeatedly drawing squares that are identical in size, with each one representing a memory. As new memories form, the older ones become obscured, fuzzy, or joined with others to form belief structures and intuitions. I hope that this work will remind you of someone, someplace, a song or a melody that’s important to you. 

Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view in live mode.
[1] to [8] Change resolution, 1.5K to 12K.
[G] Toggle paper texture.

URL params:
aspect: custom aspect ratio (?aspect=3).
res: custom resolution multiplier (?res=4).

Made with fractal math and p5js, Memory Module is the first in a 5-part generative art series about introspection. You can read more about the series here: https://elsifthen.github.io/

Created by elsif, 2022.07.

metadata.name: Nishikigoi #112
metadata.description:
A calm exploration of generative koi ponds.
Infinitely procedurally animated.

Nishikigoi recreates the meditative experience of watching swimming koi. You may click to feed your koi fish, but only once every 30 minutes.

I hope you enjoy this little experience.

metadata.name: Unicorn #725
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.
